Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways and
thinly slice.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #ovenproof saucepan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an
> ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and stir-fry until golden, ~{3-4%mins}.

Add the leek and cook until soft, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%mins}.

Once the veg has softened, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir in the
garlic. Cook for ~{1%min} more.

Stir in the @risotto rice{175%g} and cook until the edges of the rice are
translucent, ~{1-2%mins}.

Add the boiled @water for the risotto{450%ml}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and
@wild mushroom paste{15%g} to the pan. Stir well to combine.

Bring back to the boil, then pop a lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and
bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water
has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Once your risotto's ready, remove it from your oven.

Vigorously stir in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and
@unsalted butter{30%g} until melted.

Taste and add salt, pepper and a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Spoon your risotto into #bowls{} and crumble over the @goat's cheese{75%g}.

Drizzle the @wild rocket{20%g} with a little @olive oil{}, then top each bowl
with a handful to finish.

Enjoy!